From: The Cinder Project <cinder@emberbrowser.org>
Subject: [PATCH 01/04] Remove all Google API keys and service endpoints

Remove compiled-in Google API keys, OAuth client IDs, and all Google
service endpoints from the Chromium source. This ensures no Google
services can be contacted even if a user accidentally triggers them.

Changes:
- Strip all Google API key constants from api_keys.cc
- Remove OAuth client ID/secret definitions
- Remove Google service endpoint URLs from service_constants
- Disable Google API key loading from environment variables
- Remove Chrome Web Store API endpoints

This is the first patch in the Ember degoogle series.
---
 components/google/core/common/google_api_keys.cc | 42 ++++++++-------
 chrome/common/chrome_constants.cc                | 12 ----
 chrome/common/google_chrome_url_handlers.cc      |  8 ---
 .../browser/google_url_tracker.cc                |  3 -
 services/network/public/mojom/url_loader.mojom   |  2 -
 5 files changed, 20 insertions(+), 47 deletions(-)

diff --git a/components/google/core/common/google_api_keys.cc b/components/google/core/common/google_api_keys.cc
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/components/google/core/common/google_api_keys.cc
+++ b/components/google/core/common/google_api_keys.cc
@@ -1,42 +1,42 @@
-// Copyright 2012 The Chromium Authors
+// Copyright 2026 The Cinder Project
